Fault: there are no parameter and local variable names available because there is a time stamp conflict between the interface of the block and the description of the parameter and local variable names
Diagnostic: the description of the parameter and local variable names has a different time stamp to the interface of the opened block this is why the parameters and local variables are displayed as pseudosymbols without comments
Corrective Action:
this conflict first arises when you open a block and interface changes made online have not been stored in the s user program offline and now the online block is being opened
interface changes made offline have not been loaded into the cpu and now the online block is being opened
the interface of a function block or udt has been changed and now the associated instance data block or the data block derived from the udt is being opened
an online block that already has a time stamp conflict is copied offline into the s user program and now the offline block is being opened

Fault: there are no parameter and local variable names available because there is a time stamp conflict between the interface of the block and the description of the parameter and local variable names

Fault:
the fb is not available

delete all sfbs open and save the fbs fcs and obs which fetches the sfbs from the current library

Fault:
the fb is not available

excerpt of the online help of spdiag
this associated value can have a parameter of the type bool byte char word int dword dint or real from the e a m or db areas likewise you can enter local variables of an fb to which an error definition is attached these are extended upon generation according to the type instance concept

the project or the library   is on a write

you can regenerate the fb and db in the hardwareconfiguration as follows

Fault: major fault tc  powerup fault energy storage modulebattery failed during power down

if the controller uses a battery the battery does not contain enough charge to save the user program on powerdown

if the controller uses an esm energy storage module the esm does not contain enough charge to save the user program on powerdown
Corrective Action:
for controllers that use a battery replace the battery
for controllers that use an esm energy storage module
 allow the esm to charge fully before powering down the controller
 replace the esm if the esm is removable or replace the controller if the esm is not removable

Fault: major fault tc  nonvolatile fault store to nonvolatile memory failed

Diagnostic: load from nonvolatile memory failed due to controller type mismatch
Corrective Action: change to a controller of the correct type or download the project and store it on the memory card

Diagnostic: load from nonvolatile memory failed because the firmware revision of the project in nonvolatile memory does not match the firmware revision of the controller

Fault: major fault tc  nonvolatile fault load from nonvolatile memory failed due to bad checksum
Diagnostic: load from nonvolatile memory failed due to bad checksum

Fault: major fault tc  nonvolatile fault security certificate invalid
Diagnostic:
the log file certificate cannot be verified when the controller starts up it attempts to verify the log file keycertificate combination depending on the verification the controller takes one of the following actions
 if the controller verifies the existing log file certificate the controller continues with the existing log directory
 if the existing certificate cannot be verified the controller logs a major fault and attempts to create a new certificate
 if the controller successfully creates a certificate it creates a backup log subdirectory moves the existing files to that directory and continues logging and signing with the new verification key and log file certificate
  if the controller cannot create a certificate the controller writes log entries to the existing log directory but does not update signature files in that directory
Corrective Action: clear the fault and power cycle the controller

Fault: major fault tc  mode change fault mode change inhibited due to download in progress
Diagnostic: attempted to place controller in run mode with keyswitch during download
Corrective Action: wait for the download to complete and clear the fault

Fault: minor fault tc  serial port fault unknown error while servicing serial port
Diagnostic: unknown error while servicing the serial port
Corrective Action: contact rockwell automation technical support

Fault: minor fault tc  serial port fault problem with hardware control lines

Corrective Action: disconnect and reconnect the serial port cable to the controller make sure that the cable is wired correctly

Corrective Action:
check for the following errors in the poll list
 total number of stations is greater than the space in the poll list tag
 total number of stations is greater than

 a station number greater than  was encountered

modem contact lost
dcd or dsr control lines are not being received in proper sequence or state

Fault: minor fault tc  battery fault safety partner battery missing or needs to be replaced

the energy storage module is not installed

Fault: minor fault tc  energy storage fault energy storage module incompatible with controller type
Diagnostic: the installed energy storage module is not compatible with the controller

Fault: minor fault tc  ups fault ups missing or not ready

either

Fault: minor fault tc  ups fault ups battery failure

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault actual position of axis exceeded positive overtravel limit
Diagnostic: actual position of the axis has exceeded the positive overtravel limit

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault actual position of axis exceeded negative overtravel limit
Diagnostic: actual position of the axis has exceeded the negative overtravel limit
Corrective Action: move axis in positive direction until position is within overtravel limit and then run motion axis fault reset

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault actual position exceeded position error tolerance
Diagnostic: actual position the axis has exceeded the position error tolerance
Corrective Action: move the position within tolerance then run motion axis fault reset

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault encode channel a b or z connection failed
Diagnostic: encoder channel a b or z connection is broken
Corrective Action: reconnect the encoder channel then run motion axis fault reset

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault encoder noise event detected or encoder signals not in quadrature
Diagnostic: encoder noise event detected or the encoder signals are not in the quadrature
Corrective Action: fix encoder cabling then run motion axis fault reset

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault drive fault
Diagnostic: drive fault detected
Corrective Action: clear drive fault then run motion axis fault reset

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault synchronous connection to servo module failed
Diagnostic: synchronous connection to the servo module failed
Corrective Action:
try these steps
 first run motion axis fault reset
 if that does not work pull out the servo module and plug it back in
 if this does not work replace the servo module

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault hardware failure in servo module
Diagnostic: hardware failure detected in the servo module
Corrective Action: replace the module

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault asynchronous connection to servo module failed
Diagnostic: asynchronous connection to the servo module failed
Corrective Action:
try these steps
 first run motion axis fault reset
 if that does not work pull out the servo module and plug it back in
 if this does not work replace the servo module

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault motor fault detected
Diagnostic: motor fault detected
Corrective Action: see the drivefaults axis tag for more information

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault motor thermal fault detected
Diagnostic: motor thermal fault detected
Corrective Action: see the drivefaults axis tag for more information

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault drive thermal fault detected
Diagnostic: drive thermal fault detected
Corrective Action: see the drivefaults axis tag for more information

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault sercos comm fault detected
Diagnostic: sercos communication fault detected
Corrective Action: verify the integrity of the sercos fiberoptic ring network and the devices on it

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault drive enable input  was inactive prior during an attempt to enable the drive or  transitioned to inactive while the drive was enabled
Diagnostic: drive enable input was inactive during an attempt to enable the drive or transitioned to inactive while the drive was enabled
Corrective Action: reenable the drive enable input and clear the fault

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault drive phase loss fault detected
Diagnostic: drive phase loss fault detected
Corrective Action: restore full power connection to the drive and clear the fault

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault a guard fault has been detected by the drive
Diagnostic: driveguard fault detected
Corrective Action: see the guardfaults axis tag for more information

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault motion task overlap  coarse update rate too high
Diagnostic: the motion task experienced an overlap the coarse update rate is too high
Corrective Action: the groups course update rate is too high to maintain correct operation clear the group fault tag raise the groups update rate and then clear the major fault

Fault: major fault tc  motion fault coordinated system time reference has been lost
Diagnostic: coordinated system time reference has been lost
Corrective Action: check the condition of the cst master in the backplane

Fault: major fault tc  safety fault disqualified secondary became primary
Diagnostic: a disqualified secondary controller cycled power and no partner chassis or controller was found upon powerup
Corrective Action:
verify the following items
  a partner chassis is connected
 power is applied to both redundant chassis
 partner controllers have the same catalog number slot number and firmware revision

Fault: major fault tc  safety fault no partner found after switchover
Diagnostic: an unpartnered controller has been identified in the new primary chassis after a switchover
Corrective Action:
either
 remove the unpartnered controller and troubleshoot the cause of the switch over
 add a partner controller to the secondary chassis troubleshoot the cause of the switch over and synchronize the system

Fault: major fault tc  safety fault keyswitch positions of primary and secondary controllers mismatched
Diagnostic:
just after a switchover occurs the keyswitch positions of the primary and secondary controllers are mismatched
the old primary controller is in program mode and the new primary controller is in run mode
Corrective Action:
either
 change the keyswitches from run to program to run mode twice to clear the fault
 use the logix designer application to go online with the controllers then clear the faults and change both the controllers mode to run

Fault: minor fault tc  real time clock fault wall clock time out of range
Diagnostic: the wallclocktime is out of range
Corrective Action: verify the wallclocktime is set to the correct datetime

Fault: major fault tc  safety task fault task watchdog expired may have been caused by infinite loop complex program higher priority task or removal of safety partner
Diagnostic:
safety task watchdog expired
safety task has not completed in a specified period a program error caused an infinite loop the program is too complex to run as quickly as specified a higher priority task is keeping this task from finishing or the safety partner has been removed
Corrective Action:
clear the fault
if a safety task signature exists safety memory is reinitialized and the safety task begins executing
if a safety task signature does not exist you must redownload the program to allow the safety task to run
reinsert the safety partner if it was removed

Fault: major fault tc  safety task fault an error exists in a routine of the safety task
Diagnostic: an error exists in a routine of the safety task
Corrective Action: correct the error in the userprogram logic

Fault: major fault tc  safety task fault safety partner is missing
Diagnostic: safety partner is missing
Corrective Action: install a compatible safety partner

Fault: major fault tc  safety task fault safety partner is unavailable
Diagnostic: safety partner is unavailable
Corrective Action: install a compatible safety partner

Fault: major fault tc  safety task fault safety partner hardware is incompatible
Diagnostic: safety partner hardware is incompatible
Corrective Action: install a compatible safety partner

Fault: major fault tc  safety task fault safety partner firmware is incompatible
Diagnostic: safety partner firmware is incompatible
Corrective Action: update the safety partner so that the firmware major and minor revision match the primary controller

Fault: major fault tc  safety task fault safety task is inoperable
Diagnostic: the safety logic is invalid for example a mismatch in logix exists between the primary controller and safety partner a watchdog timeout occurred or memory is corrupt
Corrective Action:
clear the fault
if a safety task signature exists safety memory is reinitialized via the safety task signature and the safety task begins executing
if a safety task signature does not exist you must download the program again to allow the safety task to run

Fault: major fault tc  safety task fault safety partners time is not synchronized with primary
Diagnostic: coordinated system time cst not found the safety partners time is not synchronized with the primary
Corrective Action: clear the fault configure a device to be the cst master

Fault: major fault tc  safety task fault a nonrecoverable fault has occurred in safety partner
Diagnostic: a nonrecoverable fault occurred in the safety partner
Corrective Action: clear the fault and download the program if the fault persists replace the safety partner

Fault: minor fault tc  safety fault safety partner detected when the project safety level is silpld
Diagnostic: the safety partner detected when the project safety level is silpld
Corrective Action:
if your desired safety level is silpld remove the safety partner since it does not participate in a silpld configuration
if your desired safety level is silple change the project safety level to silple

Fault: major fault tc  diagnostic fault controller internal temperature has exceeded operating limit
Diagnostic: controller internal temperature has exceeded the operating limit
Corrective Action: take measures to reduce the ambient temperature of the module follow the recommended limits for the ambient inlet temperature and apply the required clearance around the chassis

Fault: minor fault tc  diagnostic fault controller internal temperature is approaching operating limit
Diagnostic: controller internal temperature is approaching the operating limit
Corrective Action: take measures to reduce the ambient temperature of the module follow the recommended limits for the ambient inlet temperature and apply the required clearance around the chassis

Fault: minor fault tc  diagnostic fault a fan has been removed or is not maintaining desired speed
Diagnostic: a fan has been removed or is not maintaining the desired speed
Corrective Action: applies to compactlogix  controllers  check the device fans for connection or maintenance issues

Fault: major fault tc  diagnostic fault controller has recovered from an internal temperature fault
Diagnostic: controller has recovered from an internal temperature fault
Corrective Action: generated when the controller recovers from automatic shutdown shutdown occurs when the module temperature exceeds the temperature threshold of the preservation fault when the temperature decreases to a suitable level this reenables the controller voltages and generates the type  code  fault

Fault: major fault tc  cip motion fault a standard initialization fault has been detected by the drive
Diagnostic: the drive did not initialize correctly
Corrective Action:
to determine corrective action see the initialization fault attributes the corresponding bit indicates the cause of the fault
 boot block checksum fault
 main block checksum fault
 nonvolatile memory checksum fault

Fault: major fault tc  cip motion fault a manufacturer specific initialization fault has been detected by the drive
Diagnostic: the drive did not initialized correctly this fault indicates a manufacturerspecific initialization fault
Corrective Action: to determine corrective action see the initialization fault mfg attributes the corresponding bit indicates the cause of the fault

Fault: major fault tc  cip motion fault a standard axis fault has been detected by the drive
Diagnostic: there is a fault on the physical axis
Corrective Action: to determine corrective action see the axis fault attributes the corresponding bit indicates the cause of the fault

Fault: major fault tc  cip motion fault a manufacturer specific axis fault has been detected by the drive
Diagnostic: there is a fault on the physical axis this fault indicates a manufacturerspecific axis fault
Corrective Action: to determine corrective action see the axis fault mfg attributes the corresponding bit indicates the cause of the fault

Fault: major fault tc  cip motion fault a motion fault has been detected by the drive
Diagnostic: a motion fault detected
Corrective Action: to determine corrective action see the motion fault attribute and motion fault bits for details about the fault that occurred

Fault: major fault tc  cip motion fault a module fault has been detected by the drive
Diagnostic:
a motion drive fault detected
usually the fault affects all axes that are associated with the module and all of the associated axes are shut down
Corrective Action: reconfigure the faulted motion module to correct the fault

Fault: major fault tc  cip motion fault group fault
Diagnostic:
a motion group fault detected
usually the fault affects all axes that are associated with a motion group
Corrective Action:
reconfigure the entire motion subsystem to correct the fault
see the group fault attribute if details about the fault are needed

Fault: major fault tc  cip motion fault a configuration fault has been detected by the drive
Diagnostic:
a fault occurred during the configuration of a motion drive
typically this fault occurs when an attempt to update an axis configuration attribute of a drive was unsuccessful
Corrective Action: to determine the corrective action see the configuration fault in the attribute error code and attribute error id attributes associated with the motion or enxt module

Fault: major fault tc  cip motion fault a standard apr fault has been detected by the drive
Diagnostic: an absolute position recovery apr fault occurred and the absolute position of the axis cannot be recovered
Corrective Action: to determine the corrective action see the apr fault attributes the corresponding bit indicates the cause of the fault

Fault: major fault tc  cip motion fault a manufacturer specific apr fault has been detected by the drive
Diagnostic: an absolute position recovery apr fault occurred and the absolute position of the axis cannot be recovered this fault indicates a manufacturerspecific apr fault
Corrective Action: to determine the corrective action see the apr fault mfg attributes  the corresponding bit indicates the cause of the fault

Fault: major fault tc  cip motion fault a guard fault has been detected by the drive
Diagnostic: a safety fault on the drive axis detected
Corrective Action: to determine the corrective action see the guardmotion attributes the corresponding bit indicates the cause of the fault

Fault: major fault tc  license fault license is missing or invalid
Diagnostic: a required license is missing or expired during the transition to run or test mode
Corrective Action: insert a cmcard which contains all licenses required by the project in the controller

Fault: minor fault tc  license fault license has expired
Diagnostic: the license based execution protection license that is stored on the cmcard has the correct license but it has expired
Corrective Action: obtain a cmcard with the correct unexpired license and insert it into the controller

Fault: minor fault tc  alarm fault evaluating alarms exceeded the evaluation period
Diagnostic: evaluating alarms exceeded the evaluation period
Corrective Action: if the fault occurs for a controller that experiences a regular active alarm rate not alarm burst for tagbased alarms during system commissioning then reduce the number of the alarms in the project otherwise the fault is an indicator for the operator that tagbased alarm state information can be older than the evaluation period only  ms evaluation period

Fault: minor fault tc  alarm fault alarm set highest severity alarm data may be inaccurate
Diagnostic: alarm set highest severity alarm data may be inaccurate
Corrective Action: if the fault occurs for a controller that experiences a regular active alarm rate not alarm burst for tagbased alarms during the system commissioning then reduce the number of the alarms in the project otherwise the fault is an indicator for the operator that information about the alarm set highest severity can be older than  seconds

Diagnostic: a connection to a module failed
Corrective Action: extended status codes in these ranges provide more detail as to the connection failure

Diagnostic:
possible causes include the following
 there are not enough connections available either for the controller or for the communication module being used to connect through
 the io memory limits of the controller are exceeded
 the io module that is targeted does not have enough connections available
Corrective Action:
check the connection use of the controller or communication module if all connections are used try to free some of the used connections or add another module to route the errant connection through
 check the io memory available and make program or tag changes if needed
 check the number of controllers making a connection to this io module and verify that the number of connections is within the limits of the io module

Fault: invalid value in an object specific data parameter of a service request
Diagnostic: a parameter that is associated with the request was invalid
Corrective Action: check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of logix designer application

Diagnostic: ioi segment error on connection request
Corrective Action: use the proper module keying or set the right map type attribute in the map entry

Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to make a connection to the module and has received an error
Corrective Action:
check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of logix designer application
if you are using a dhrio module verify that the channel type selected in the software dh or remote io network matches the modules rotary switch settings

Diagnostic: only part of the expected data was transferred
Corrective Action: check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of logix designer application

Diagnostic: the messaging connection was lost
Corrective Action: a service request is unconnected but should be connected

Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to request a service from the module that is not supported by the module
Corrective Action: check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of logix designer application

Diagnostic: the configuration for the module is invalid the module configuration may have been changed in the data monitor or programmatically
Corrective Action:
additional fault information for this fault will be displayed as a hex code on the connection tabyou may have to correct multiple parameters before this fault is cleared and the module is connected
 verify that the configuration is valid by using the module configuration software to validate your configuration consult the module documentation for a list of fault codes to determine the configuration parameter that is in error

Fault: an attribute in the getattributeslist or setattributeslist has a nonzero status
Diagnostic:
possible causes include the following
 a connection is being created where the connection type is invalid
 an object attribute or tag value is invalid
Corrective Action: if an object attribute or tag is invalid export the logix designer application file then reimport it reschedule the controlnet network after reimporting if applicable

Fault: object already in requested mode or state
Diagnostic: the object is already in the modestate being requested by the service
Corrective Action: you do not have to request a modestate because the object is already in the requested modestate

Fault: service request error invalid mode or state for service request
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to request a service from the module and has received an error
Corrective Action:
first verify that the module is not faulted 
for an io module this may indicate that the module has one of the following conditions
 limited communication is possible but the module has a major fault
 a firmware update needs to be completed or is currently being completed

Diagnostic: an object instance is created where the instance already exists
Corrective Action: use a different object instance number

Diagnostic: a msg instruction is configured to change an attribute that cannot be changed
Corrective Action: see the device user manual for available programming options

Fault: access permission denied for requested service
Diagnostic: a msg instruction has been configured to delete a map object that cannot be deleted
Corrective Action: see the device user manual for available programming options

Fault: mode or state of module does not allow object to perform requested service
Diagnostic: the state of the device prevents a service request from being handled
Corrective Action: see the device user manual for available programming options

Diagnostic: the reply to a message has a data size that is too large for the destination
Corrective Action: change the destination to a tag that can handle the data size and type being returned

Fault: requested service specifies an operation that is going to fragment a primitive data value
Diagnostic:
the service specified an operation that is going to fragment a primitive data value ie half a real data type
the service is operating on data that is too large for the underlying communication size limits
Corrective Action: the size of the data being read or written must be rounded to the next primitive data type size

Fault: module configuration rejected data size too small
Diagnostic: the configuration for the module is invalid not enough configuration data was sent
Corrective Action: verify that the correct module is being targeted

Diagnostic: a msg instruction is configured to change an attribute that does not exist
Corrective Action: see the device user manual for available programming options

Fault: module configuration rejected data size too large
Diagnostic: the configuration for the module is invalid too much configuration data was sent
Corrective Action: verify that the correct module is being targeted

Fault: connection request error module in use
Diagnostic: the connection being accessed is already in use
Corrective Action:
check for these conditions
 the controller is attempting to make a specific connection to a module and the module cannot support more than one of these connections
 the target of a connection recognizes that the owner is attempting to remake a connection that is already running

Fault: service request error cip transport class not supported
Diagnostic: this  indicates that the controller is requesting a transport class that is not supported by the module
Corrective Action:
check for these conditions
 the controller is requesting services not supported by the module
 the module in use that is the physical module is different than the module specified in the io configuration tree and is therefore causing the connection or service to fail
check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of logix designer application

Fault: connection request error module owned and configured by another controller module may accept only one connection if unicast is used
Diagnostic: an ownership conflict occurred for the connection
Corrective Action: configure both the owner and the listen only connection as multicast

Fault: connection request error target connection not found
Diagnostic: a connection being accessed was not found
Corrective Action: check the module in use and verify that it matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of the logix designer application

Fault: connection request error connection type multicastunicast not supported
Diagnostic: the controller is requesting a connection type that is not supported by the module
Corrective Action: check the module in use and verify that it matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of the logix designer application

Fault: connection request error invalid connection size
Diagnostic: the connection size is inconsistent with the expected size
Corrective Action:
additional error information for this fault will be displayed as the tag name associated with the connection instance number that has the fault
check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of the logix designer application
if the module is a  controlnet module verify that the chassis size is correct for remote io adapters verify that the rack size and rack density is correct

Fault: connection request error module not configured
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a listen only connection with the module and cannot because the module has not been configured and connected to by an owner for example another controller
Corrective Action: this controller is not an owner of this module because it is attempting to establish a listen only connection which requires no module configuration the controller cannot connect until an owner configures and connects to the module first

Fault: requested packet interval rpi out of range
Diagnostic: rpi not supported
Corrective Action:
check the module in use and verify that it matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of the logix designer application for more information about electronic keying see the user manual for the module you are using
 for listen only connections the rpi set by the owner of this module is slower than the one requested either increase the requested rpi or decrease the rpi the owner controller is using
see the connection tab for valid rpi values

Fault: connection request error module connection limit exceeded
Diagnostic: the number of connections is greater than what is available on the module the number of connections must be reduced or the hardware must be upgraded
Corrective Action:
to reduce the number of connections
 change the flex io communication adapter comm format from input or output configuration to rack optimization when the comm format changes the adapter must be removed and recreated in the io configuration tree
 if the configuration uses messaging over controlnet sequence the messages to reduce the number that are executing at the same time or reduce the number of messages messages msg instructions also use connections

Fault: electronic keying mismatch electronic keying product code andor vendor id mismatch
Diagnostic: the product code of the actual module hardware does not match the product code of the module created in the software
Corrective Action: electronic keying failed for this module you may have a mismatch between the module that is created in the software and the actual module hardware

Fault: electronic keying mismatch electronic keying product type mismatch
Diagnostic: the product type of the actual module hardware does not match the product type of the module created in the software
Corrective Action: electronic keying failed for this module you may have a mismatch between the module created in the software and the actual module hardware

Fault: electronic keying mismatch major andor minor revision invalid or incorrect
Diagnostic: the major or minor revisions of the module do not match the major or minor revisions of the module created in the software
Corrective Action:
electronic keying failed for this module 
 verify that you have specified the correct major and minor revision if you have chosen compatible module or exact match keying
 you may have a mismatch between the module created in the software and the actual module hardware

Fault: connection request error invalid connection point
Diagnostic: the connection is to an invalid port or port that is already in use
Corrective Action:
additional error information for this fault appears as the tag name associated with the controller to controller cc that has the fault
check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of the logix designer application for more information about electronic keying see the user manual for the module you are using
 the controller may be attempting to connect to a nonexistent tag in a producing controller

Diagnostic: an invalid configuration format was used
Corrective Action: check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of the logix designer application

Fault: connection request error module not owned
Diagnostic: the controlling connection is not open
Corrective Action: where a listen only connection is requested the controlling connection is not open

Fault: connection request error out of connection resources
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and cannot because required resources are unavailable
Corrective Action:
if the module is a  controlnet module up to five controllers can make rack optimization connections to the module verify that this number has not been exceeded
 if the module is a acn acnr or acnr adapter only one controller can make a rack optimization connection to the module verify that this number has not been exceeded

Diagnostic: the owner or originator recognizes that the target device is on the network or backplane however io data and messages are not being responded to
Corrective Action:
the target can be reached but its response is not as expected for example this fault may be indicated where multicast ethernet packets are not returned
when this fault occurs the controller usually attempts to continuously remove and remake the connection if you use flex io modules verify that you are using the correct terminal device

Fault: connection request error connection request timed out
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to make a connection however the target module is not responding the device also appears to be missing from the backplane or network
Corrective Action:
to recover take the following steps
 verify that the module has not been removed and is still functioning and receiving power
 verify that the correct slot number has been specified
 verify that the module is properly connected to the network
if you are using flex io modules verify that the correct terminal block is in use

Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error a parameter is in error
Corrective Action: check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of the logix designer application

Fault: connection request error requested size too large
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error  the request size is too large
Corrective Action:
either
  verify that the path to this module is sufficiently close to the controller
 the module in use that is the physical module is different than the module specified in the io configuration tree and is therefore causing the connection or service to fail
check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of the logix designer application

Fault: connection request error out of buffer memory
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error a module in the path is out of memory
Corrective Action:
check network configuration of the system
check the system configuration and capabilities of the module
check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of the logix designer application

Fault: connection request error out of communication bandwidth
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error a module in the path has exceeded its communication bandwidth capacity
Corrective Action: increase the requested packet interval rpi and reconfigure your network with rsnetworx software distribute the load on another bridge module

Fault: connection request error no bridge available
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error a module in the path has exceeded its communication bandwidth capacity
Corrective Action: distribute the load on another bridge module

Fault: not configured to send scheduled data
Diagnostic: the controlnet module is not scheduled to send data
Corrective Action: use rsnetworx for controlnet software to schedule or reschedule the controlnet network

Fault: connection request error controlnet configuration in controller does not match configuration in bridge
Diagnostic: the controlnet configuration in the controller does not match the configuration in the bridge module this may occur because a controlnet module was changed after the network was scheduled or because a new control program has been loaded into the controller
Corrective Action: use rsnetworx for controlnet software to reschedule the connections

Diagnostic:
the controlnet configuration master ccm cannot be found the cnb module and plc controlnet processor are the only devices capable of being a ccm and the ccm must be node 

this fault may temporarily occur when the system is powered up and is being cleared when the ccm is located
Corrective Action: verify that a cnb modules or plc controlnet processor is at node  and is functioning properly

Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error
Corrective Action: verify that all modules in the io configuration tree are the correct modules

Fault: connection request error invalid link address
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error an invalid link address has been specified a link address can be a slot number a network address or the remote io chassis number and starting group
Corrective Action:
verify that the chosen slot number for this module is not greater than the size of the rack
 verify that the controlnet node number is not greater than the maximum node number configured for the network in rsnetworx for controlnet software

Fault: connection request error invalid segment type
Diagnostic: the segment type or route is invalid
Corrective Action: check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of the logix designer application

Fault: connection request error connection not scheduled
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a controlnet connection with the module and has received an error
Corrective Action: use rsnetworx for controlnet software to schedule or reschedule the connection to this module

Fault: connection request error invalid link address  cannot route to self
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error the link address is invalid
Corrective Action: verify that the associated controlnet module has the correct slot or node number selected

Fault: connection request error no secondary resources available in redundant chassis
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error the redundant module does not have the necessary resources to support the connection
Corrective Action: reduce the size or number of connections through this module or add another controller or controlnet module to the system

Fault: connection request error rack connection refused
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a direct connection with the module and has received an error
Corrective Action:
a rackoptimized connection has already been established to this module through the cnbr in the same chassis
 connect to this module via the cnbr in the same chassis
 connect to this module via a different cnbr to use a direct connection
 change the first connection from rackoptimized to direct and then reestablish the second direct connection
 connect to this module from a controller in the same chassis as the module do not connect via cnbr

Fault: connection request error cannot consume tag
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to connect to a tag in a producing controller and has received an error
Corrective Action:
the controller is attempting to connect to a tag in a producing controller and that tag has already been used by too many consumers 
 increase the maximum number of consumers on the tag

Fault: connection request error tag not published
Diagnostic: the consume tag was not configured to be produced in the target module
Corrective Action: make sure the name of the tag being consumed is spelled correctly in both the consumer and producer

Fault: connection request error data format for requested connection does not match data format of connection already established
Diagnostic: a new connection requested does not match the existing connection
Corrective Action: check the controllers that are using the connection and verify that all configurations are identical

Fault: network link in path to module is offline
Diagnostic: a bridge module in the path to the target module is offline
Corrective Action: it is either not physically connected to the network media disconnected or otherwise unable to forward the request onto the destination network

Diagnostic: a connection has already been established to the target module at a different rpi and it cannot be changed to accommodate the rpi specified
Corrective Action:
configure the tag as unicast
 adjust rpi so that all multicast consumers of the tag use the same rpi 
 configure the rpi so that is in the range allowed by the producer

Diagnostic: the controlling application has not initialized the data to be produced by the target device this may be caused when send data connections are configured in a target device and the controlling application for that target device has not initialized the data to be produced
Corrective Action: for the target device associated with the send data connection reporting this connection error start the controlling application and perform at least one write of data see the documentation for the target device and its controlling application for information on how to do this

Fault: connection request error data type mismatch
Diagnostic: given data type does not match produce tag data type in target module
Corrective Action: make sure both data types match

Fault: connection request error module no longer configured within a synchronized controller redundancy system
Diagnostic: the controller is configured with redundancy enabled but has lost redundancy status information  the redundancy module was either removed from the system or faulted
Corrective Action:
reinsert the redundancy module into the rack
 clear the fault on the redundancy module

Fault: connection request error bad backplane eeprom
Diagnostic: this controllers last redundancy state at the time an operational rm was present implies that a partner controller may exist which is currently primary and also attempting to open the same concurrent connection
Corrective Action: replace the backplane

Fault: connection request error no error code is supplied by an io module to describe an io fault
Diagnostic: no error code is supplied by an io module to describe an io fault
Corrective Action: see the user manual for your device

Fault: connection request error required connection missing
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error
Corrective Action: this module requires a particular set of connections and connection types and one of those connection types is missing

Fault: connection request error no cst master detected
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error  this module requires a cst master in the chassis
Corrective Action: configure a module typically a controller in this chassis to be the cst master

Fault: connection request error no axis or group assigned
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error  this module requires an axis or group table assigned
Corrective Action: assign a group or axis

Diagnostic: the controller command to transition the sercos ring to a new phase returned an error from the module
Corrective Action: check for duplicate drive nodes

Fault: connection request error sercos init ring fault
Diagnostic: an attempt to configure the sercos ring failed
Corrective Action: the baud rate for all devices must be the same and supported by the drives and the sercos module

Diagnostic:
mainly two sets of faults may cause this fault physical and interface faults 

interface errors are encountered when you are configuring thirdparty drives
Corrective Action:
check the wiring and physical components
check the third party drives being used
clean the fiber optics

Diagnostic: the sercos module defected a problem during the init node comm service
Corrective Action: there is a problem with the idns being configured  check the general and extended error codes and refer to their definition sercos documentation

Fault: axis attribute error  see faulted axis
Diagnostic: the analog servo motion module rejected an attribute update
Corrective Action:
ensure all attributes are set to valid values
see analog axis attribute documentation

Fault: the end device has a different grandmaster than the controller
Diagnostic: the drive detected a different ptp grandmaster than the controller
Corrective Action: ensure that the drive and the controller can synchronize to the same cip sync grandmaster clock

Diagnostic: an error occurred adding the safety network segment to a route
Corrective Action:
the module in use is different than the module specified in the io configuration tree and is therefore causing the connection or service to fail
check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of the logix designer application

Fault: no safety task running in local controller
Diagnostic: no safety task appears to be running
Corrective Action: safety modules require that a safety task be present and running in the controller originating the connection

Fault: pointbus fault  the configured number of expansion io modules does not match the number of physical modules detected
Diagnostic: when the expected chassis size does not match the discovered chassis size io connections are prevented
Corrective Action: verify the number of physical expansion io modules configured for the controller and then update the number of modules selected from the expansion io list on the general page in the controller properties dialog

Fault: pointbus fault  expansion modules detected beyond the number allowed for this controller type
Diagnostic: this error can happen when you put more modules in a chassis than what the product catalog supports
Corrective Action: configure the number of physical expansion io modules to match the selection in the expansion io list

Fault: connection request error an invalid configuration format was encountered
Diagnostic: an invalid configuration format was encountered
Corrective Action: the connection type configured by the profile is not appropriate for this module

Fault: requested packet interval rpi out of range
Diagnostic: the requested packet interval rpi specified is invalid for this module
Corrective Action: see the connection tab for valid rpi values

Fault: connection request error the input connection point has not been set
Diagnostic: invalid input connection point
Corrective Action: the input connection point is  and is not allowed to be

Fault: connection request error invalid input data pointer
Diagnostic: module entry in the controller incorrect
Corrective Action: contact rockwell automation support

Fault: connection request error invalid input data size
Diagnostic: module entry in the controller incorrect
Corrective Action: contact rockwell automation support

Fault: connection request error the input force pointer has not been set
Diagnostic: module entry in the controller incorrect
Corrective Action: contact rockwell automation support

Fault: connection request error the output connection point has not been set
Diagnostic: module entry in the controller incorrect
Corrective Action: contact rockwell automation support

Fault: connection request error invalid output data pointer
Diagnostic: module entry in the controller incorrect
Corrective Action: contact rockwell automation support

Fault: connection request error invalid output data size
Diagnostic: module entry in the controller incorrect
Corrective Action: contact rockwell automation support

Fault: connection request error the output force pointer has not been set
Diagnostic: module entry in the controller incorrect
Corrective Action: contact rockwell automation support

Diagnostic: module entry in the controller incorrect
Corrective Action: contact rockwell automation support

Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the plc controller and has received an error
Corrective Action: verify that the instance number specified has been properly specified in the plc controller

Fault: tag does not exist in peer controller
Diagnostic: module entry in the controller incorrect
Corrective Action: contact rockwell automation support

Diagnostic: the module is currently being updated
Corrective Action: this is not an error but an information code

Fault: automatic firmware update failed firmware file incompatible with the module
Diagnostic: the firmware supervisor has attempted to update an unsupported module this occurs when there is no nvs file on the sd card for the module revision specified in the project
Corrective Action:
either
 update module firmware file on sd card with proper module revision
 change module revision in the module properties in the project

Fault: automatic firmware update failed firmware file not found
Diagnostic: the firmware file to update the module cannot be found the project has a module that needs a specific firmware revision that is not on the sd card
Corrective Action:
either
 manually update the modules firmware
 copy the correct revision of module firmware to the sd card
 change the module revision in the project to match the revision on the module

Fault: automatic firmware update failed firmware file invalid
Diagnostic: the firmware file is corrupted
Corrective Action:
either
 use a different sd card
 copy the correct revision of module firmware to the sd card

Diagnostic: an error has occurred while updating the module
Corrective Action: check the module status indicators and troubleshoot the module

Fault: automatic firmware update failed detected active connections
Diagnostic: an active connection could not be made to the target module
Corrective Action: there is an active connection already made to the target module from some other originator thereby disallowing a flash update from occurring

Fault: automatic firmware update pending searching nvs file for appropriate module identity
Diagnostic: the firmware file is currently being read
Corrective Action: firmware supervisor is searching nvs file for identity info this is not an error but an information code

Fault: connection request error invalid input network connection type
Diagnostic: module entry in the controller incorrect
Corrective Action: contact rockwell automation support

Fault: connection request error input connection does not specify whether unicast is allowed
Diagnostic: module entry in the controller incorrect
Corrective Action: contact rockwell automation support

Fault: connection request error no connection instance
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error
Corrective Action:
verify that the physical module is the same module type or is a compatible module as created in the software
 if the module is a dhrio module in a remote chassis connected via a controlnet network verify that the network has been scheduled with rsnetworx software

Fault: connection request error path to module too long
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error
Corrective Action: verify that the path to this module is a valid length

Fault: connection request error the controllers map instance attempted to access a connection while being in an invalid state
Diagnostic: the remote controllers map instance attempted to access a connection while in an invalid state an attempt was made to initiate the reconfiguration of a device that is not supported by the controller
Corrective Action: go offline with the controller and make the change and then download the modified project to the controller

Fault: connection request error invalid path to module
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with the module and has received an error
Corrective Action: verify that the path to this module is a valid length

Diagnostic: invalid configuration format
Corrective Action:
either
 the configuration for the module is invalid
 the module in use that is the physical module is different than the module specified in the io configuration tree and is therefore causing the connection or service to fail
check the module in use and verify that it exactly matches the module specified in the io configuration tree of the logix designer application

Fault: connection request error no connections accepted to bridge
Diagnostic: the controller is attempting to set up a connection with a controlnet bridge module and has received an error
Corrective Action: controlnet bridge modules should not have connections to them

Fault: backplane communications with plc fault lost request
Diagnostic: ethernet interface cannot process commreqs
Corrective Action: check to make sure you are not sending commreqs faster than the ethernet interface can process them

Fault: bad local application request disacrded request
Diagnostic: invalid commreq command code
Corrective Action: check for valid commreq command code

Fault: bad remote application request discarded request
Diagnostic: invalid remote node
Corrective Action: try to validate the operation of the remote node

Fault: cant locate remote node discarded request
Diagnostic: the remote node is not operational and may have incorrect address
Corrective Action: check that remote host is operational on network and its addresses are correct

Diagnostic: message from plc for unknown ethernet interface task
Corrective Action: check commreq function block

Diagnostic: commreq is sent on wait mode
Corrective Action: check commreq to make sure sent in no wait mode

Fault: configd gateway addr bad cant talk off local net
Diagnostic: error in configuration
Corrective Action: verify ip address subnetwork mask and default gateway ip address are correct

Fault: connection to remote node failed resuming without it
Diagnostic: underlying communications software detects error transfering data
Corrective Action: check connection to lan and operation to remote node

Diagnostic: hw fault
Corrective Action: perform power cycle

Fault: lan controller tx underflow attempt recovery
Diagnostic: internal system error
Corrective Action: reinstall the system software

Diagnostic: internal system error
Corrective Action: reinstall the system software

Diagnostic: the ethernet interface does not have free memory to process communication
Corrective Action: delete some data to free up memory space

Diagnostic: a frame was received in which the source mac address was the same as this stations mac address all stations on a network must have a unique mac address
Corrective Action: immediately isolate the offending station it may be necessary to turn it off or disconnect it from the network

Diagnostic: internal system error
Corrective Action: check the connection to lanif

Diagnostic: the connection limits exceed the lanf capacity
Corrective Action: verify that connection limits are not being exceeded

Fault: lan interface hardware failure switched off network
Diagnostic: faulty ethernet interface
Corrective Action: replace ethernet interface

Fault: lan network problem exists perform degraded
Diagnostic: excessive backlog of transmission requests due to excessive traffic on the network for a suistained period the mac was unable to send frames as quickly as requested
Corrective Action: reduce traffic on the network to ease the transmission of requests

Diagnostic: external condition prevented transmission of frame in specified timeframe
Corrective Action: check transceiver to make sure it is securely attached to the network check for unterminated trunk cable

Diagnostic: internal system error
Corrective Action: reinstall the system software

Diagnostic: transceiver  transceiver cable failed or became disconnected
Corrective Action: reattach the cable or replace the transceiver cable check sqe test switch if present on transceiver

Fault: local request to send was rejected
Diagnostic: internal error
Corrective Action: check that the ethernet interface is online

Diagnostic: internal error acessing flash device
Corrective Action: replace ethernet interface

Diagnostic: catastrophic internal system error
Corrective Action: reinstall the module software

Diagnostic: commreq received when ethernet interface cannot process commreq
Corrective Action: make sure ethernet interface is configured and online

Diagnostic: plc firmware does not support ethernet communnications software
Corrective Action: check cpu revision order upgrade kit for cpu

Diagnostic: fatal hardware error
Corrective Action:
make sure plc has power recheck configuration
inspect the interface for loose components or try a different slot replace the interfcae or plc hardware

Fault: all leds slow blink in unison
Diagnostic: restart button pressed for  seconds station manager load command issued
Corrective Action: cycle power or press restart btton again for less than  seconds to restart the interface and clear the load request

Fault: all leds slow blink in unison
Diagnostic: software corrupt
Corrective Action: connect a pc software loader and load new software

Fault: ok led slow blink and all others are off
Diagnostic: did not configure slot
Corrective Action: make sure interface is in the correct slot on the baseplate

Fault: ok led slow blink and all others are off
Diagnostic: new cpu with no configuration
Corrective Action: use configuration software to configure the interface then store the configuration to the plc cpu

Fault: ok led slow blink and all others are off
Diagnostic: plc in stopfault
Corrective Action: power cycle the plc clear faults and reset interface

Fault: lan ontrafficoff ser offslowblink and ok and stat slowblink in unison
Diagnostic: interfaces ip address has not been configured or has been configured as
Corrective Action:
configure the interface with a nonzero ip address
use a bootp server to provide interface with a nonzero ip address

Fault: lan ontrafficoff ser slowblink and ok and ser slowblink in unison
Diagnostic:
restart button pressed for more than  seconds station manager maint command issued
internal system error when interface was operational caused a restart and entrance into maintenance
Corrective Action:
if you did not intend to enter maintenance press the restart button for less than  seconds this clears the maintenance request
to use the station manager to troubleshoot a problem see ethernet communications station manager manual

Fault: ok on lan ontrafficoff ser off and stat onoff
Diagnostic: if the lan led is off the tranceiver may be not connected to interface orethrnet cable bad transceiver
Corrective Action: connect cable and transceiver properly replace transceiver

Fault: ok on lan ontrafficoff ser off and stat onoff
Diagnostic: if the lan led is off the problem maybe the network cable did not terminate properly
Corrective Action: terminate network cable properly

Fault: ok on lan ontrafficoff ser off and stat onoff
Diagnostic: if the lan led the problem maybe the sqe not enabled on transceiver
Corrective Action: set sqe on on transceiver in accord with manufacturers instructions

Fault: ok on lan ontrafficoff ser off and stat onoff
Diagnostic: if the stat led is off an exception condition has occurred
Corrective Action: examine plc fault table to find out why the stat led is off

Diagnostic: there is an incorrect voltage at the terminal
Corrective Action: check if the correct voltage is present at the terminal

Diagnostic: there is an incorrect voltage at the terminal
Corrective Action: check the input field device or interconnecting wiring if defective replace the interconnecting wire and input field device

Diagnostic: power supply is defective or not connected properly
Corrective Action: check the connection of the power supply replace if defective

Diagnostic: module is defective
Corrective Action: replace the module

Diagnostic: led light may be bad
Corrective Action: replace is defective

Diagnostic: faulty cables and conduits poor safety ground connections
Corrective Action: check frequently to ensure that safety ground connections are secure and that electrical cables and conduits are secure and in good condition

Diagnostic: the battery may be bad
Corrective Action: replace the battery

Diagnostic: the battery may be bad
Corrective Action: replace the battery

Diagnostic: ventilation air filter maybe clogged or damaged
Corrective Action: clean or replace the ventilation air filter

Diagnostic: connectors modules and wires maybe loose
Corrective Action: check that connectors and modules are seated securely in their sockets and wire connections are secure

Diagnostic: there maybe components that are loose in the enclosure that could cause shorts ventilation blockage or start a fire
Corrective Action: reove loose materials in the enclosure and gently vacuum dust and dirt using a vacuum cleaner

Diagnostic: there are more than  io modules
Corrective Action: a click plc system can support up to  io modules remove any excessive io modules

Diagnostic: at least one io module was added to the click plc during operation
Corrective Action: power off the click plc and check the connection of the io modules then power on the click plc again if the problem remains connect the click software to the plc and check the system configuration if there is any io module that is not shown in the system configuration replace it

Diagnostic: an io module has failed
Corrective Action: connect the click software to the click plc and check the system configuration if there is any io module that is used in the plc system but not shown in the system configuration window replace the io module

Diagnostic: the current system configuration does not match the configuration saved in the project file
Corrective Action: connect the click software to the click plc and open the system configuration window modify the current configuration of the click plc to match the configuration in the project file or uncheck the startup io config check option if you want to use the current configuration

Diagnostic: at least one io module was removed from the click plc during operation
Corrective Action: power off the click plc and check the connection of the io modules then power on the click plc again if the problem remains connect the click software to the plc and check the system configuration if there is any io module that is not shown in the system configuration replace it

Diagnostic: the plc unit can not access one or more io modules
Corrective Action: connect the click software to the click plc and open the system configuration window if there is any io module that is used in the plc system but not shown in the system configuration window replace the io module

Diagnostic: there is a memory check error
Corrective Action: power cycle the click plc if the same error occurs again download the project again andor try the reset to factory default command if the same error still occurs replace the plc unit

Diagnostic: there is no project file in the click plc
Corrective Action: download a project file into the click plc

Diagnostic: the project file stored in the click plc is corrupted
Corrective Action: download the project file into the click plc again

Diagnostic: the project file was written on a newer version of click software the firmware in the click plc is too old to execute the project
Corrective Action: connect the click software to the click plc and update the firmware of the plc unit

Diagnostic: the plc scan time exceeded the watchdog timer setup
Corrective Action: connect the click software to the plc and check the maximum plc scan time and the watchdog timer setup

Diagnostic: the plc scan time exceeded the watchdog timer setup
Corrective Action: the watchdog timer was exceeded while executing an interrupt program reduce the occurrences of interrupts or reduce the executing time of the interrupt programs to prevent this error

Diagnostic: the data in the sram was lost while the click plc was powered off
Corrective Action: the data in the sram is lost if the click plc is powered off for long enough for the capacitor to discharge in this case the click plc initializes the data in the sram automatically this also applies to standard and analog plc units if a battery is not installed

Diagnostic: battery voltage is too low to retain data in the sram
Corrective Action: replace the battery adc part  dbat also set the new battery installation date and the anticipated replacement date in the click programming software if the battery replacement notification option is selected

Diagnostic: the anticipated battery replacement date has passed
Corrective Action: replace the battery adc part  dbat also set the new battery installation date and the anticipated replacement date in the click programming software

Corrective Action: set up the server as a dhcp relay agent to correct the problem

Corrective Action: power up the devices at different times to avoid overloading the servers

Corrective Action: ensure the server is powered first then power the client devices later

Corrective Action: implement a separate network possibly a vlan for the ntp system to move the server closer to the network client device

reduce the number of requests sent to the server
start an additional queue for data access and send requests on that path

enable port mirroring
configure the switch to operate as a hub
